history.content: When I took 188, the readings were not very emphasized, especially in the textbook. If you attend lecture, much of the time that is sufficient to learn the material for the first time, in my experience (was not so for CS70, for example). I would recommend reviewing the provided course notes (not textbook readings) after lecture if there was something you didn't fully understand during lecture.

children.subject: Reading the book isn't necessary at all. Definitely go over the lecture and lecture materials as well as the notes the post

history.content: How important is doing the readings for 188? Of course, I know readings always help but if they're not as important as reading the notes for say, CS 70, then I just want to prioritize my time better.
history.subject: Readings for 188 Importance?
